The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | BTTA issues a threat
                                                                                                                       7                                      BTTA issues a threat
            A STAFF REPORTER                            
	Calcutta: The Bengal Table Tennis Association (BTTA), on Saturday, threatened to oppose the national championships to be played here in January if their players were not considered for selection.         
	The BTTA, which was deaffiliated by the Table Tennis Federetion of India (TTFI), called for unification of the three operating associations (BTTA, West Bengal Table Tennis Association (WBTTA) and the North Bengal Table Tennis Association (NBTTA)) and end the discrimination.         
	Speaking to the media on Saturday, former state and national coach Diptimoy Mukherjee, said: There cant be three state championships in one state. Our players shouldnt be discriminated against.         
	According to Mukherjee, the BTTA will take up the issue with the sports minister and has plans for legal measures, in case, their players continue to be neglected.                                                                                                                     
